<Author>Eml012881
<Content>Wonderful Hotel I stayed at Hotel de las Letras on my first trip to Madrid and loved it. I think it was the perfect choice as a hotel. I loved the location both in terms of walking distance to places as well as to to the metro. My room was on a higher floor and overlooked the side street off of the Gran Via. WIth the windows closed, I experienced no noise from the street. For a single room, I found the size to be larger than expected. The bed was comfortable and the bathroom was really nice. Wished there had been more light in the room at night. Breakfast was a delicious but at 14 euros a little pricey everyday. I also had drinks in the bar/cafe at night which was nice if I didn't want to walk too far. I found the staff very helpful. I was there over Easter and they provided me with information on events occuring in the city. They also booked my ticket for the theater which I thought was a very nice touch. I would easily stay here again! 
