<Content>Good overall, probably not 3rd best in the city though. I stayed in this hotel for 5 nights for work, but I had extended my stay to enjoy a weekend in Madrid. Overall I had a pleasant stay. The reception were very helpful when I needed advice about getting a prescription, although I did think it quite odd that there is nowhere to sit down around the reception area. I was regularly waiting for colleagues and had to nowhere really to wait downstairs unless I went to the bar. The breakfast which was included in our rate was quite good, a wide selection of fruits, pastries, juices, cheeses, hams etc.The room was spacious enough, I would agree that it was quite dark ( no proper mirror for putting on makeup) but I quite liked it, as everything was really new and clean. The spa area was fine, although the floor was very wet. Also, despite the rather deceptive photograph, this hotel does NOT have a pool!I think the location is great for Madrid - right on Grand Via, 5 mins to Puerta del Sol and between two great areas for restaurants. I would stay in this hotel again and enjoyed my stay, but I doubt it should be the 3rd highest rated hotel in Madrid, or maybe the standards in the city aren't very high. 
