<Content>Loved this hotel Spent 48 hours in Madrid.Fab staff, great bar and restaurant. Very cool but not in a self conscious way (like some hotels I've posted reviews on). The spa was very good also.Based in the Central area, this is within walking distance of everything; museums, restaurants, night-life.The hotel is well maintained, with a wonderful upbeat reception staff. I had a problem accessing WiFi which was dealt with immediately. Reservations, recommendations, etc etc all handled with charm and genuine affection by staff. Unique I suspect these days. There were some really stressed peeps checking out when I was checking in (their cab was 5 mins late) and that worried me. It shouldn't have. Their nationality might have given me a clue.... Hint, hint... And the staff handled it all impeccably. Madrilenos are famously laid back, so the cigarette smoke can get to you, the wait for a coffee/drink drive you to distraction and the national sport of queue jumping leave you feeling crapped upon but at this hotel, you'll feel loved. And the best indicator of all were the locals who popped in top use the bar/restaurant during the day and nite. And a few familiar famous peeps dropped into say hello to their friends.The secret? Be nice and they'll be nice right back. Simple really. 
