<Author>1972j
<Content>Hotel de les Letras is great We recently spent 5 nights at the Hotel de les Letras. It's a terrific place to stay. The design is very chic- it reminds you of a more upscale W hotel- although it's much nicer and on a much more managable scale than a W or other similiar large chain hotel. The rooms are large by big city standards (comparable or larger than most rooms I've stayed at in NYC, Paris, London, etc.). The bathroom we had was really large, with two sinks, and was well appointed. We also had a balcony overlooking the Gran Via and even though the street is busy, noise was not an issue. The room came equipped with a small couch, desk, and a flat screen tv with english language stations. And, one of the best perks was that there is a free wireless internet connection.The hotel itself is in a perfect location. You can walk any where in the city easily- to the museums, royal palace, to shopping- or you can hop on a metro stop (there are 3 near-by). There are lots of great restaurants within a 5 minute walk in the Chuerca district. The front desk was great at offering dining tips  on bars that were worth checking out.If you are travelling with others, the hotel's restaurant/bar has a great lounge area to meet up or wait for others.All in all, I thought the Hotel de les Letras was one of the best places I've stayed in Europe- I would highly recommend it to anyone. It's worth visiting Madrid just to stay at the hotel. 
