<Author>briguy2006
<Content>Comfortable and convenient, with just a couple kinks We just returned from two weeks in Spain, including four nights in Madrid. I would definitely recommend Hotel de las Letras to anyone planning a visit to the Spanish capital. Our rooms (we stayed in one room at the start of our vacation and another room our last night in Spain) were spacious, stylishly decorated and comfortable, the buffet breakfast was good, the hip and happening terrace bar offered a nice view and a pleasant breeze, and the location was perfect for the kinds of sightseeing we, as Madrid newbies, wanted to do. Still, a few small details kept it from being a 5-star experience. By themselves, none of these details would be worth mentioning, but it was the accumulation of them that nudged the hotel down to a 4-star level for us. First, our balcony had no furniture when we first got there, so we had to call down to the front desk to have some deck chairs brought up (they brought one chair and one table). What's the point of having a large balcony if you can't sit out there? Then the next day we had to call down for a bottle opener so we could open some drinks that were in the mini bar, and we also discovered that the housekeeping staff had emptied the ice tray, so there was no ice for our drinks. One night we asked about the gym, only to discover that it was basically a couple pieces of equipment and that, for some reason, it would only be open for about an hour that night. Luckily we didn't want to work out that badly. Most troublesome was that some of the staff bordered on surly. The unattentive woman who was supposed to serve the coffee during breakfast got kind of huffy when we beckoned her over to get our first cup of coffee halfway through our meal, and the people working the bar the one night we went up there seemed pretty frazzled and anything but friendly. Again, none of these events was that big a deal, but it's those small details that make the difference between a 4-star and 5-star experience. Maybe with a little more time they'll iron out some of these rough spots. 
