<Content>Magnificence in Madrid With a quotation by Octavio Paz floating on our burnt orange walls, we were immersed in the true spirit of the Hotel de las Letras, which has quips from Spanish novelists and philosophers in every room and in every hallway. Smack dab in the middle of Madrid on the Gran Via, the hotel was perfectly located for our art attack tour of the city: Museo Thyssen, Museo de Prado, and the Queen Sofia museum which houses Guernica (back in Madrid, just as Picasso indicated in his will). Front staff booked a day tour for us to Toledo, and was very courteous and forthcoming with all manner of travel info. We walked everywhere, including dinners in various parts of the city, and always felt safe returning to our hotel after midnight.Our room had a king-size bed with a perfect mattress, crisp white linens, and an ultra mod bathroom complete with hip towel warmers, trough sink, and cool amenities. The only tricky part is negotiating the 1-volt LED mini-elevator that takes you and your luggage up to your floor, but even that was charming. This hotel is a must for Madrid! 
