<Content>Loved the hotel, but the restaurant was another story... We got some very cheap flights to Madrid, and on the strength of that I looked on Tripadvisor for a hotel better than I could usually afford - Las Letras had good reviews and was close enough to the places we wanted to visit. What was good? - Well, the room was lovely, very clean (and I am very fussy!); every facility, even a small sofa with footstool; well designed so that there was a lobby area with the wardrobe and bathroom and another door then thru to the bedroom, thus less noise from corridor; aircon - needed it; rooftop bar was one of the best features, it was a lovely place to have predinner drinks, cool breeze and views across the city; breakfast was great - huge selection including spanish omelette and local hams, as well as all the usual suspects; even found the little library in the basement, with internet access if needed; must also mention the reception staff who were fantastically helpful and friendly in every respect, nothing was too much trouble. The only thing that went very wrong for us was our meal in the restaurant on our last night - we thought it would be easier to stay at the hotel for the whole evening as we had our bags to carry, we could have drinks on the roof, then just go down to the restuarant. This was a big mistake. Soup was lukewarm, did not say anything as did not want to ruin last evening. Ordered fish with green salad and balsamic, and boiled new potatoes. What I got was some fish which managed to be overcooked but still almost cold, a small handful of salad leaves from a mixed bag with cheap olive oil on them, and FOUR cold chips! When I pointed out that the chips were cold, the waitress offered to have them 'warmed up'! Asked her to bring some hot ones, but by the time they came I had given up - the rest of the food was practically inedible anyway. No-one bothered to ask if the food was ok, the waitress just avoided us until we asked for the bill, then asked if we wanted to speak to the manager - well, no, but I would have loved to speak to the so-called chef! Others may have a different experience, and in fairness I would have to say that the bar snacks/tapas looked nicer than the meals we were served. I would just say, stay at this hotel by all means, it deserves its good reviews - but avoid the restaurant - except for breakfast I wouldn't eat there again if I was paid 拢100 to do so. 
